Vice President Biden will be traveling to Erie, Pennsylvania on July 1st to highlight the broadband investments made through the Recovery Act. He will be joined by Secretary of Commerce Gary Locke, Secretary of Agriculture Tom Vilsack, Federal Communications Commission Chairman Julius Genachowski, Congresswoman Kathy Dahlkemper, and other local officials. The event is open to the public on a first-come, first-served basis. Media must RSVP by June 30th to attend. The event will take place at Seneca High School in Erie, PA.